INSERT INTO `BNOTES` VALUES ('BGN',2,1999,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 116 х 64 mm\r%NL%Main Colour: purple\r%NL%Paper: 100% cotton','','0299f.jpg','0299b.jpg','','The major item on the obverse side: an engraving of Pagisios of Chiliandar.  The background depicts the Zografou Monastery on Mount Athos, the Monastery Seal, and the interior of Pagisios\' monastic cell.\r%NL%%NL%The reverse side shows a facsimile of the Zografou draft of the of the “Historiae Sclavo-Bulgaricus” with a list of Bulgarian rulers. This is overprinted with impressions of Tsar Kalogiannis Ring Seal and three seals with the images of Bulgarian Sovereigns Mihail Shishman, Svetoslav Terter and Tsar Ivan Asen II. The right side shows Hristofor Zhefarovich\'s lion rampant with the names of Bulgarian rulers from the First and Second Empires overprinted in microscopic lettering, Bottom right appears Bulgaria\'s Coat of Arms with three lions couchant, as published in the Gruenberg Heraldic Compendium of 1483.\r%NL%%NL%Source::BNB %NL%www.bnb.bg%NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-4750 of 18.04.2006.','','',33),('BGN',2,2005,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 116 mm х 64 mm\r%NL%Paper: 100% cotton, toned in blue\r%NL%','','0205f.jpg','0205b.jpg','','Bulgarian Bank issued modified 2-levs banknote on 6 of December 2006. \r%NL%\r%NL%The dimensions, colours, design, security elements are unchanged. The banknote is dated 2005 and the signatures are updated. \r%NL%The paper: 100% cotton, in blue tones. It\'s durability is improved. \r%NL%\r%NL%Banknotes of emission 1999 remain valid.\r%NL%\r%NL%Source::BNB %NL%www.bnb.bg\r%NL%\r%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-4750 of 18.04.2006.\r%NL%','','',1134),('BGN',2,2015,'М',NULL,'Тегло: 9 г\r\nДиаметър: 26.5 мм\r\nГурт: редуващи се назъбени и гладки сектори','','c0215o.jpg','c0215.jpg','','','','',1731),('BGN',2,2018,'M',NULL,'Тегло: 9 г\r\nДиаметър: 26.5 мм\r\nГурт: редуващи се назъбени и гладки сектори','','m218f.jpg','m218b.jpg','','','','',1890),('BGN',5,1999,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 121 х 67 mm\r%NL%Main Colour: claret\r%NL%Paper: 100% cotton','','0599f.jpg','0599b.jpg','E','Main feature of the obverse side of the banknote is the engraving of Ivan Milev, a noted Bulgarian 1920s artist. The background shows details of his painting \"Art and the Crown of Thorns\", decorative motifs from his other works, passages from his letters and a monogram from a bill advertising his first exhibition, held in Sofia in 1925.\r%NL%\r%NL%The reverse shows fragments from his paintings “A Woman Harvesting”, “The Bulgarian Madonna”, and “Wedding of the Dragon”.\r%NL%\r%NL%Source: Bulgarian National Bank%NL%www.bnb.bg%NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-4750 of 18.04.2006.','','Elements of the pattern, serial numbers and fibres in the paper fluoresce under UV light.',34),('BGN',5,2009,'',NULL,'Dimensions:   121 mm х 67 mm\r%NL%Main Colour:    claret\r%NL%Paper:   100% cotton','','052k9f.jpg','052k9b.jpg','','Bulgarian Bank issued modified 5-levs banknote on 1st of June 2009 \r%NL%The dimensions, colours, design, security elements are unchanged. The banknote is dated 2009 and the signatures are updated. \r%NL%Some changes in the security features:%NL%NL% - improved Copy Prevention Stripe and Security Thread;\r%NL%- added a Hidden image - at a viewing angle 15 - 20 degrees, the words “5 ЛЕВА” (5 LEVS) appear on the right of the holographic stripe;\r%NL%- added second watermark - contrasting inicials “БНБ” (BNB);\r%NL%- added UV-Visible Bi-Fluorescent Ink.\r%NL%\r%NL%Banknotes of emission 1999 remain valid.\r%NL%\r%NL%Source::BNB%NL%www.bnb.bg%NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-11890 of 22.06.2009.','','',1513),('BGN',10,1999,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 126 х 70 mm\r%NL%Main Colour: green\r%NL%Paper: 100% cotton','','1099f.jpg','1099b.jpg','','The obverse side carries an engraving of Doctor Peter Beron. To the right of him appear the frontispiece and plates from his 1824 “Primer Containing Diverse Instructions”. Colloquially known as Riben Bukvar (the Fish Primer), this was infused with the ideas of advanced European education.\r%NL%\r%NL%The reverse side shows sketches taken from Peter Beron\'s treatises in astronomy, and his personal telescope.\r%NL%\r%NL%Source::BNB %NL%www.bnb.bg%NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-4750 of 18.04.2006.\r%NL%','','',35),('BGN',10,2008,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 126 mm x 70 mm\r%NL%Main Colour: в green','','102k8f.jpg','102k8b.jpg','','Bulgarian Bank issued modified 10-levs banknote on 8 of December 2008.%NL%The dimensions, colours, design are unchanged. The banknote is dated 2008 and the signatures are updated.%NL%Some changes in the security features:%NL%NL%- improved Hologram (Copy Prevention) Stripe and Security Thread;%NL%- added second Watermark - contrasting inicials “БНБ” (BNB) /Electrotype watermark/; %NL%- added UV-Visible Bi-Fluorescent Ink.%NL%%NL%Banknotes of emission 1999 remain valid.%NL%%NL% \r%NL%Source::BNB %NL%www.bnb.bg%NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-11890 of 22.06.2009.','','',1487),('BGN',20,1999,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 31 х 73 mm\r%NL%Main Colour: blue\r%NL%Paper: 100% cotton','','2099f.jpg','2099b.jpg','E','A portrait of Stefan Stambolov is the main feature on the obverse side of the banknote. The central part carries a cover facsimile of his anthology “Songs and Poems” issued in Bucharest in 1877, and his poem “To My Comrades”. Below appears the Seal of the Edinstvo (Unity) Committee in Tarnovo, whose co-founder Stambolov was.\r%NL%Stefan Stambolov (1854 - 1895) is a Bulgarian politician. He is considered one of the most important and popular \"Founders of Modern Bulgaria\", and is sometimes referred to as \"the Bulgarian Bismarck\". Participant in the National Liberation struggle, poet, National Unification activist, National Assembly Deputy, Chairman, Prime Minister and Regent, Stambolov put Bulgaria upon the map of European statesmanship.\r%NL%%NL%The reverse of the banknote depicts the National Assembly building and fragments of Orlov Most and Lavov Most (Sofia\'s Eagle and Lion Bridges): public edifices linked with his period in office; and manuscript in his hand.\r%NL%%NL%Source::BNB%NL%www.bnb.bg%NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-4750 of 18.04.2006.','','',36),('BGN',20,2005,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 134 mm х 74 mm\r%NL%Main Colour:  purple','','2005f.jpg','2005b.jpg','','The First Bulgarian Commemorative Banknote, issued 15 of September 2005 to celebrate 120th Anniversary of issue of Bulgarian Leva currency. The first 20-levs and 50-levs banknotes have been put into circulation on 1st of September 1885.\r%NL% They have been printed in the Saint-Petersburg Paper Mill. %NL%%NL%Paper is toned in pale violet, the background colour is violet. %NL%%NL% There is a 15-mm vertical polymer strip on the front-left side, so the banknote could be classified as a hybrid type. \r%NL%%NL%Source::BNB%NL%www.bnb.bg %NL%%NL%This banknote is reproduced here in conformity with the Ordinance No. 18/2006 of the BNB and upon written consent of the BNB  No. 4702-4750 of 18.04.2006.','','',1145),('BGN',20,2007,'',NULL,'Dimensions: 131 mm х 73 mm','','202k7f.jpg','202k7b.jpg','','Bulgarian Bank issued modified 20-levs banknote on 12 of November 2007. \r%NL%The dimensions, colours, design are unchanged. The banknote is dated 2007 and the 