INSERT INTO `BNOTESI` VALUES (32,1,'Portrait',158,146,NULL,NULL,'bgl01992.jpg','Portrait of the obverse is an image of the icon of 1789 of St. Ivan Rilski the church \"Assumption of Virgin Mary\" of hermitage \"Pchelino\" in the vicinity of the Rila Monastery.\r%NL%\r%NL%St. Ivan Rilski (876-946), one by the preachers of Christianity after its adoption as the state religion in 864, was canonized shortly after his death. In the place where he lived was founded Rila Monastery, existing more than 1,000 years, which even today treasures up the relics of the saint.\r%NL%'),(32,2,'Watermark',373,95,38,98,'bg019913.jpg','Halftone image of a rampant lion.'),(32,3,'Intaglio printing',410,108,NULL,NULL,'blank.jpg','The obverse portrait printed texts \"BULGARIAN NATIONAL BANK\", \"one lev\", the vignette and the nominal figure \"1\" on the prevention stripe.'),(32,4,'Security thread',268,28,149,205,'bg019912.jpg','Built-in paper band with negative Microtext \"БНБ\".'),(32,5,'Holographic stripe',24,156,NULL,NULL,'bgl01993.jpg','А holographic stripe, made of diamond elements that change color when changing the viewing angle.'),(32,6,'Microprint',375,183,99,189,'bgl01997.jpg','Repeated \"ЛЕВ\" to the right of the item under the nominal figure \"1\" on both sides of the note.'),(32,7,'Microprint',82,29,187,27,'bgl01998.jpg','Left of the portrait on the front lines with alternate lyrics \"ИВАН РИЛСКИ\" and \"876-946\".\n%NL%\n%NL% above the dome of the church on the back - repeated \"РИЛСКИ МАНАСТИР ЕДИН ЛЕВ\"'),(32,8,'Raised Printing for the Visually Impaired',410,198,NULL,NULL,'bgl01999.jpg','Relief image of a triangle pointing up and circle underneath it.'),(32,9,'Design Elements',260,148,NULL,NULL,'bgl01995.jpg','Element of the image of the front side.'),(32,10,'Design Elements',262,185,NULL,NULL,'bgl01996.jpg','Element of the image of the front side.'),(32,11,'Paper',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'bgl01990.jpg','Built visible fibers.'),(33,1,'Portrait',130,150,NULL,NULL,'bgl02992.jpg','Paissiy Hilendarski - (1722-1773) - Bulgarian national educator, first ideologist of the Bulgarian National Revival. Born in Bansko. Endowed with an alert mind and extraordinary insight. In 1745 went to Hilendar Monastery on Mount Athos, where tonsured. As a monastery envoy toured villages and towns. The plight of the Bulgarians led him to write the history of the Bulgarian people, which ends in 1762. \r%NL%In the \"Slav-Bulgarian History\" Paissiy Hilendarski describes the glorious past, the virtues, the bravery and the culture of the Bulgarian people. The book is read, copied and distributed to all Bulgarian lands. 50 copies have been found till now.\r%NL%'),(33,2,'Watermark',361,88,38,91,'bg029913.jpg','Halftone image of a rampant lion.'),(33,3,'Intaglio printing',397,58,NULL,NULL,'blank.jpg','The obverse portrait printed texts \"BULGARIAN NATIONAL BANK\", \"TWO LEVA\" figure at face value \"2\", the vignette and the nominal figure \"2\" on the holographic strip.'),(33,4,'Security thread',251,41,149,42,'bg029912.jpg','Built-in paper band with negative Microtext \"БНБ\".'),(33,5,'Holographic stripe',35,88,NULL,NULL,'bgl02993.jpg','А holographic stripe, made of diamond elements that change color when changing the viewing angle.'),(33,6,'Microprint',75,18,315,30,'bgl02998.jpg','* To the left of the portrait repeated \"ПАИСИЙ ХИЛЕНДАРСКИ\"\n%NL%\n%NL% * In the image of the lion are listed the names of Bulgarian kings, \"ИВАН АЛЕКСАНДЪР МИХАИЛ ШИШМАН ...\".'),(33,7,'Microprint',358,183,NULL,NULL,'bgl02997.jpg','Repeated \"2 ЛЕВА\" filling the nominal figure \"2\".'),(33,8,'Microprint',191,27,NULL,NULL,'bgl02999.jpg','Vertical lines of the number \"2\" to the right of the portrait.'),(33,9,'See-through register',304,175,114,180,'bg029911.jpg','Picture of the number \"2\" is formed in a square chessboard field observation the light.'),(33,10,'Raised Printing for the Visually Impaired',412,200,NULL,NULL,'bg029910.jpg','Relief image of two rectangles.'),(33,11,'Paper',NUL