he layout of the main hall of the Norwegian National Opera in Oslo.'),(583,1,'Portrait',185,123,NULL,NULL,'20042.jpg','The seventh U.S. President (1829–37), Andrew Jackson has been featured on the front side of the bill since 1928, which is why the twenty-dollar bill is often called a \"Jackson,\" while the White House is featured on the reverse side.%NL%%NL%\n\nJackson first appeared on the $20 bill in 1928. It is not clear the reason the bill was switched from Grover Cleveland to Andrew Jackson. According to the U.S. Treasury, \"Treasury Department records do not reveal the reason that portraits of these particular statesmen were chosen in preference to those of other persons of equal importance and prominence.\"%NL%%NL%\n\nThe placement of Jackson on the $20 bill may be a historical irony; as president, he vehemently opposed both the National Bank and paper money and made the goal of his administration the destruction of the National Bank. In his farewell address to the nation, he cautioned the public about paper money.\n%NL%%NL%\nThe oval borders and fine lines surrounding the portrait of President Jackson on the front, and the White House vignette on the back, have been removed. The portrait has been moved up and shoulders have been extended into the border. Additional engraving details have been added to the vignette background.'),(583,2,'Treasury Seal',320,92,NULL,NULL,'200410.jpg','GREEN TREASURY SEAL\n%NL%  The balancing scales represent justice. The chevron with thirteen stars represents the original thirteen colonies. The key below the chevron represents authority and trust; 1789 is the year that the Department of the Treasury was established. The series 1969 dollar bills were the first to use a simplified Treasury Seal, with the wording in English instead of Latin.'),(583,3,'Federal Reserve Seal',70,85,NULL,NULL,'200411.jpg','A universal seal to the left of the portrait represents the entire Federal Reserve System. A letter and number beneath the left serial number identifies the issuing Federal Reserve Bank. There are 12 regional Federal Reserve Banks and 24 branches located in major cities throughout the United States.'),(583,4,'Security thread',40,79,NULL,NULL,'20044.jpg','Hold the bill to light and look for the security thread that is embedded in the paper and runs vertically up one side of the bill. If you look closely, the words USA TWENTY and a small flag are visible along the thread from both sides of the bill. The security thread glows green when illuminated by ultraviolet light.'),(583,5,'Watermark',387,90,NULL,NULL,'20043.jpg','Hold the bill to light and look for the watermark, or faint image, similar to the large portrait. The watermark is part of the paper itself and can be seen from both sides of the bill.'),(583,6,'Color-Shifting Ink',380,128,NULL,NULL,'20047.jpg','Tilt your bill to see if the numeral 20 in the lower right corner on the front of the bill changes color from copper to green. The color shift is more dramatic in the redesigned currency, making it easier for people to check their money.'),(583,7,'Microprint 1',270,60,NULL,NULL,'20045.jpg','Bordering the first three letters of the TWENTY USA ribbon to the right of the portrait, the inscription USA20 is printed in blue.'),(583,8,'Microprint 2',32,148,NULL,NULL,'20048.jpg','THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA 20 USA 20 appears in black on the border below the Treasurer\'s signature..'),(583,9,'Serial Numbers',74,36,NULL,NULL,'200412.jpg','The unique combination of eleven numbers and letters appears twice on the front of the bill. Because they are unique identifiers, serial numbers help law enforcement identify counterfeit notes, and they also help the Bureau of Engraving and Printing track quality standards for the notes they produce.'),(583,10,'Color and design',119,130,NULL,NULL,'2004-1.jpg','The most noticeable difference in the redesigned $20 bill is the addition of subtle background colors of green, peach and blue to both sides of the bill.%NL%%NL% This marked the first time in modern American history that U.S. currency included colors other than black and green. %NL%%NL%The words TWENTY USA are printed in blue in the background to the right of the portrait.%NL%%NL% The background colors add complexity to the bills and differ with each denomination to help distinguish them. Because color can be duplicated by potential counterfeiters, it should not be used to verify the authenticity of the bill.\n%NL%%NL%\nThe oval borders and fine lines surrounding the portrait of President Jackson on the front, and the White House vignette on the back, have been removed. %NL%The portrait has been moved up and shoulders have been extended into the border. Additional engraving details have been added to the vignette background.\n'),(583,11,'Symbols of Freedom',250,120,NULL,NULL,'20046.jpg','Appearing on the front of the bill are two American eagle symbols of freedom.%NL%%NL% The large blue eagle in the background to the left of President Andrew Jackson\'s portrait is representative of those drawn and sculpted during his time period. %NL%%NL%The smaller green metallic eagle to the lower right of the portrait is a more contemporary illustration, using the same raised ink intaglio process as the portrait, numerals and engravings. %NL%The symbols of freedom differ for each denomination.'),(583,12,'The White House',NULL,NULL,207,113,'20041.jpg','Raised print image of the White House.\n'),(583,13,'Series 2006',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'200413.jpg','Signatures on banknotes series 2006: \r%NL%Cabral (Treasurer) & H.M.Paulson (Secretary of the Treasury)'),(583,14,'Series 2009',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'200414.jpg','Signatures on banknotes series 2009: \r%NL%\r%NL%Treasurer - Rosa Gumataotao Rios  \r%NL%Secretary of the Treasury: Timothy Geithner'),(583,15,'\"Star Notes\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'200415.jpg','When an imperfect note is detected during the manufacturing process after the serial number has been overprinted, it must be replaced with a new note.\n%NL%%NL% A \"star\" note is used to replace the imperfect note. Reusing that exact serial number to replace the imperfect note is costly and time consuming. %NL%%NL%The \"star\" note has its own special serial number followed by a star in place of a suffix letter.\n %NL%%NL%\nThe serial number of the imperfect note that was removed is not used again in the same numbering sequence'),(688,1,'Watermark',59,115,377,127,'dkk5h971.jpg','Watermark: halftone image of the personality of note.'),(688,2,'Security thread',181,31,NULL,NULL,'dkk5h974.jpg','There are two security threads:\r%NL%- embedded in the paper and visible against the light;\r%NL%- partially comes out the front, with Microtext \"500 KR\", which changes color to green at different angles of observation.'),(688,3,'Intaglio printing',160,74,264,94,'dkk5h973.jpg','Embossing: the front side - wall, portrait and lyrics;\n%NL% on the reverse side: the main figure.'),(688,4,'Hologram',36,58,NULL,NULL,'5h031.jpg','Hologram: Alternating images of letter \"D\" - face value of the banknote, written in Roman numerals and the image of an atom with the number 500, depending on the angle of observation.'),(688,5,'Microprint',321,90,NULL,NULL,'dkk5h975.jpg','Micro text on the front:\n%NL% - located around the watermark - the face value of the note, written in words;\n%NL% - in the fine mesh around the portrait.'),(688,6,'Paper',22,166,NULL,NULL,'2hf.jpg','Paper: embedded with fluorescent yellow-green fibers.'),(748,1,'Portrait',146,99,NULL,NULL,'1h031.jpg','Portrait: On obverse of the banknote is a portrait of the writer Aleko Konstantinov, figures and elements related to the tourist movement in Bulgaria, and the front page of the travel notes \"To Chicago and Back\".\r%NL%Оrigin: www.bnb.bg'),(748,2,'Back',NULL,NULL,231,106,'1h0317.jpg','On the reverse side are represented items related to the life and work of the writer Aleko Konstantinov.\n%NL% Author of banknote design is Cyril Gogov.\n%NL% Source: www.bnb.bg'),(748,3,'Watermark',349,91,55,99,'1h0318.jpg','Halftone image of the portrait of the bill and the initials \"BNB\" under it.'),(748,4,'Intaglio printing',102,161,NULL,NULL,'1h032.jpg','Embossing: On the obverse are printed in relief the following elements:\n%NL% - Text \"Bulgarian National Bank\"\n%NL% - Text \"Hundred lev\"\n%NL% - Text \"Aleko Konstantinov\" and \"1863 - 1897\"\n%NL% - the number of nominal \"100\"\n%NL% - portrait (most clearly felt the touch of his jacket)\n%NL% - the signature of Aleko Konstantinov\n%NL% - marked \"100 lev\" and the number \"100\" on the holographic strip.\n%NL%'),(748,5,'Security thread',256,54,157,88,'1h0319.jpg','Security thread: embedded in the paper, which partially comes on the reverse side of the banknote with negative text \"Bank 100\" and holographic effect.'),(748,6,'Holographic stripe',37,34,NULL,NULL,'1h033.jpg','A holographic strip with the following elements: \r%NL%- alternating depending on the angle of observation edelweiss and a portrait of Aleko Konstantinov in profile;\r%NL%- number of the nominal \"100\", which changes its color when changing the viewing angle;\r%NL%- texts \"ЛЕВА\" and \"БЪЛГАРСКА НАРОДНА БАНКА\", which changes its color when changing the viewing angle.\r%NL%On the hologram strip is embossed imprinted \"100 ЛЕВА\" and the number of the nominal \"100\".\r%NL%\r%NL%\r%NL%Source: website of the National Bank\r%NL%www.bnb.bg'),(748,7,'Microprint - front 1',91,18,NULL,NULL,'1h034.jpg','Microtext on the face:\r%NL%- located to the left of the portrait, alternating lines of text\"Алеко Константинов\", \"1863 - 1897\", \"Сто лева\" and \"100 лева\".\r%NL%- Located in the form of two parallel lines with repeated text \"Алеко Константинов\",left of the big inscription \"Алеко Константинов\". '),(748,8,'Microprint - front 2',251,96,NULL,NULL,'1h035.jpg','Microtext on the face:\r%NL%- in the form of curves with repeated text \"Алеко Константинов\", \"100 лева\" and \"Сто лева\" around some stylized images of people in the central part of the bill.\r%NL%- in the form of parallel lines with repeated inscription \"1863 1897\" in the images of people.'),(748,9,'Microprint - front 3',275,68,NULL,NULL,'1h038.jpg','Microtext on the face:\r%NL%-in the form of curves with repeated inscription \"1863 1897\" in stylized images of trees in the center of the banknote.'),(748,10,'Microprint - front 4',235,197,NULL,NULL,'1h036.jpg','Microtext on the face:\r%NL%- in the form of line - repeated \"Bulgarian National Bank\", to the left of the hologram band;\r%NL%- number of nominal \"100\" woven into ornamental green strip to the left of the portrait of Aleko Konstantinov;\r%NL%- repeated the number of nominal \"100\" in the form of thin lines forming bar to the left of edelweiss.'),(748,11,'Microprint - front 5',345,167,NULL,NULL,'1h037.jpg','Text \"100 ЛЕВА\" filling up the number of nominal \"100\".'),(748,12,'Microprint - back 1',NULL,NULL,194,23,'1h0312.jpg','Microtext on the back side:\r%NL%- repeating text \"БНБ\" and \"100\" woven into the ornament at the top center of the banknote.'),(748,13,'Microprint - back 2',NULL,NULL,112,180,'1h0313.jpg','Microtext on the back side:\r%NL%- repeating text \"Българска народна банка\" in form of line, placed right of the inscription \"За подправка виновните се наказват съгласно закона\";\r%NL%- repeating text \"Щастливеца 100\" as a line, left of the Aleko Konstantinov face;\r%NL%- repeating text \"БНБ\" and the nominal number \"100\" in the patterned green vertical bar at the left of the security thread.'),(748,14,'Microprint - back 3',NULL,NULL,144,203,'1h0314.jpg','Microtext on the back side:\r%NL%- repeating text \"Българска народна банка Сто лева 100 лева\" as a paralel lines, located in a small yellow square under the image of an open book;\r%NL%- repeating text \"Българска народна банка 100 лева\", located in a rectangle left of the the above-described component.'),(748,15,'Microprint - back 4',NULL,NULL,222,187,'1h0315.jpg','Microtext on the back side: \r%NL%placed in the image of an open book.'),(748,16,'Microprint - back 5',NULL,NULL,316,108,'1h0316.jpg','Microtext on the reverse side:\r%NL%as lines in the jacket of Aleko Konstantinov.'),(748,17,'Color-Shifting Ink',268,166,NULL,NULL,'1h0310.jpg','Part of edelweiss is printed in ink with variable color changes from purple to green when changing the viewing angle.\n%NL%\n%NL% With the naked eye can see the profile of Aleko Konstantinov.'),(748,18,'See-through register',298,127,117,132,'1h039.jpg','Picture of the number \"100\" is formed in a rectangular chessboard field observation the light.'),(748,19,'Raised Printing for the Visually Impaired',410,197,NULL,NULL,'1h0311.jpg','Relief image of a triangle and a rectangle.'),(785,1,'Intaglio printing',380,34,NULL,NULL,'cad1t371.jpg','Embossing:\n%NL% - recto: portrait and large numbers of par in the upper corners of the face;\n%NL% - downside: the central image and the large number of par on both sides.'),(785,2,'Microprint',252,150,NULL,NULL,'cad1t372.jpg','Micro text: in the background of the banknote.'),(785,3,'Paper',380,100,NULL,NULL,'cad01373.jpg','Paper: incorporating small Greenest Planchettes (elements).\r%NL%They mix with the paper pulp still in the process of production of the paper. Can be seen as small green dots that can be removed from the surface of the banknote with a sharp object and remove left a white dot on the note.\r%NL%Counterfeits do not have this property.'),(786,1,'Intaglio printing',400,25,385,56,'blank.jpg','Embossing:\n%NL% - on the front - portrait and the numbers in the corners of the face value of the note;\n%NL% - the reverse - the main image and the numbers of par.'),(786,2,'Portrait',350,145,NULL,NULL,'blank.jpg','Portrait of Queen Elizabeth II'),(786,3,'Paper',2,94,2,104,'cad50751.jpg','Paper: incorporating small Greenest Planchettes (elements) which fluoresce when illuminated with UV-rays.\r%NL%They mix with the paper pulp still in the process of production of the paper. Can be seen as small green dots that can be removed from the surface of the banknote with a sharp object and remove left a white dot on the note.\r%NL%Counterfeits do not have this property.'),(787,1,'Intaglio printing',400,30,216,109,'blank.jpg','Embossing:\n%NL% - on the front - portrait and the numbers in the corners of the face value of the note;\n%NL% - the reverse - the main image and the numbers of par.'),(787,2,'Portrait',346,125,NULL,NULL,'cad05721.jpg','Portrait of Sir Wilfrid Laurita - the first French-Canadian prime minister elected in the period 1896 - 1911.'),(787,3,'See-through register',25,95,NULL,NULL,'cad05792.jpg','See through register: When held against the light has exactly matching elements on both sides of the note.'),(787,4,'Paper',5,70,16,15,'cad50751.jpg','Paper: incorporating small Greenest Planchettes (elements) which fluoresce when illuminated with UV-rays.\r%NL%They mix with the paper pulp still in the process of production of the paper. Can be seen as small green dots that can be removed from the surface of the banknote with a sharp object and remove left a white dot on the note.\r%NL%Counterfeits do not have this property.'),(826,1,'Portrait',177,108,NULL,NULL,'50041.jpg','The 18th U.S. President (1869–77), Ulysses S. Grant, is featured on the obverse of the note, while the U.S. Capitol is featured on the reverse.\n%NL%%NL%\nA fifty dollar bill is sometimes called a Grant, based on the use of Ulysses S. Grant\'s portrait on the bill.\n%NL%%NL%\nThe oval borders and fine lines surrounding the portrait of President Grant on the front and the vignette of the United States Capitol Building on the back have been removed. The portrait has been moved up and shoulders have been extended into the border. Additional engraving details have been added to the vignette background.'),(826,2,'Treasury Seal',310,78,NULL,NULL,'50042.jpg','GREEN TREASURY SEAL\n%NL%  The balancing scales represent justice. The chevron with thirteen stars represents the original thirteen colonies. The key below the chevron represents authority and trust; 1789 is the year that the Department of the Treasury was established. '),(826,3,'Federal Reserve Indicators',72,80,NULL,NULL,'50043.jpg','A universal seal to the left of the portrait represents the entire Federal Reserve System. A letter and number beneath the left serial number identifies the issuing Federal Reserve Bank. There are 12 regional Federal Reserve Banks and 24 branches located in major cities throughout the United States.'),(826,4,'Security thread',245,76,138,80,'50044.jpg','Hold the bill to light and look for the security thread that is embedded in the paper and runs vertically up one side of the bill. If you look closely, the words USA 50 and a small flag are visible along the thread from both sides of the bill. The security thread glows yellow when illuminated by ultraviolet light.'),(826,5,'Watermark',395,80,48,80,'50045.jpg','Watermark: Hold the bill to light and look for the watermark, or faint image, similar to the large portrait. The watermark is part of the paper itself and can be seen from both sides of the bill.'),(826,6,'Microprint 1',110,90,NULL,NULL,'50046.jpg','Microtext 1:  the words FIFTY, USA, and the numeral 50 can be found in two of the blue stars to the left of the portrait.'),(826,7,'Microprint 2',3,104,NULL,NULL,'50047.jpg','Microtext 2: the word FIFTY can be found repeated within both side borders of the bill.'),(826,8,'Microprint 3',165,137,NULL,NULL,'50048.jpg','Microtext 3: the words THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA appear on President Ulysses S. Grant\'s collar, under his beard.'),(826,9,'Color-Shifting Ink',380,130,NULL,NULL,'50049.jpg','Tilt the bill to see if the numeral 50 in the lower right corner on the front of the bill changes colors from copper to green. The color shift is more dramatic in the redesigned currency making it even easier for people to check their money.'),(826,10,'Serial Numbers',90,30,NULL,NULL,'500410.jpg','The unique combination of eleven numbers and letters appears twice on the front of the bill. On the redesigned $50 bill, the left serial number has shifted slightly to the right, compared with previous designs. Because they are unique identifiers, serial numbers help law enforcement identify counterfeit notes, and they also help the Bureau of Engraving and Printing track quality standards for the notes they produce.'),(826,11,'Color and design',360,85,NULL,NULL,'500411.jpg','The most noticeable difference in the redesigned $50 bill is the addition of subtle background colors of blue and red to both sides of the bill. The background colors add complexity to the bills and differ with each denomination to help distinguish them. Because color can be duplicated by potential counterfeiters, it should not be used to verify the authenticity of the bill.%NL%%NL%\n\nSymbols of freedom have been added to the design on the front of the $50 bill to represent images of the American flag. The traditional stars and stripes of the United States flag are printed in blue and red behind the portrait of President Grant. A field of blue stars is located to the left of the portrait, while three red stripes are located to the right of the portrait. A small metallic silver-blue star is located on the lower right side of the portrait. The symbols of freedom differ for each denomination.%NL%%NL%\n\nThe oval borders and fine lines surrounding the portrait of President Grant on the front and the vignette of the United States Capitol Building on the back have been removed. The portrait has been moved up and shoulders have been extended into the border. Additional engraving details have been added to the vignette background.\n.\n\n'),(826,12,'Series 2006',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'500412.jpg','Signatures on banknotes series 2006: \r%NL%Cabral (Treasurer) & H.M.Paulson (Secretary of the Treasury)'),(826,13,'Series 2009',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'500413.jpg','Signatures on banknotes series 2009: \r%NL%\r%NL%Treasurer - Rosa Gumataotao Rios  \r%NL%Secretary of the Treasury: Timothy Geithner'),(826,14,'\"Star Notes\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'500414.jpg','When an imperfect note is detected during the manufacturing process after the serial number has been overprinted, it must be replaced with a new note.\n%NL%%NL% A \"star\" note is used to replace the imperfect note. Reusing that exact serial number to replace the imperfect note is costly and time consuming. %NL%%NL%The \"star\" note has its own special serial number followed by a star in place of a suffix letter.\n %NL%%NL%\nThe serial number of the imperfect note that was removed is not used again in the same numbering sequence'),(853,1,'Front',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'520041.jpg','Recto:\n%NL% elements that distinguish this bill from the regular 5-pound note of Royal Bank are the emblem of the clubhouse (ROYAL & ANCIENT GOLF CLUB OF S\'ANDREWS) printed embossed on the left side with gold ink and specific prefix to the serial number \" R & A \"(from the\" Royal and Ancient \"). This combination of characters is familiar to golfers worldwide.\n%NL% below the image of the emblem is printed year of establishment of the club - 1754.\n%NL% Royal Bank (Royal Bank of Scotland) notes this anniversary, as it was the 250th anniversary is very important for Scottish elite circles, and suggest that the first manager of the bank Elaine Lord (whose portrait is presented on the face of the note ) was a golfer (Scotland game is known from 1457) It is interesting to know that the Royal bank of Scotland is even older than the golf club - was established in 1727 by royal decree.\n%NL%%NL% A little bit of history of the club:\n%NL%%NL% R & A (Royal and Ancient Golf Club of St Andrews) is a private golf club of elite golf - society. It is not only one of the oldest golf club, but the master core of golf on the majority of the world.\n%NL% It is based in St Andrews, Scotland - a place considered the \"home\" of golf.\n%NL% beginning the c