e monastery Hilendar. Here Paisij tonsured. Became priest, and in 1759 he was elected abbot of the monastery. Around 1760 Paisij began working in the libraries of Mount Athos on historical essay \"History of Slavs.\" In 1761 traveled to Karlowitz (then in Austria) to collect additional material about the past of the Bulgarian people. Upon return he moved to Zograph monastery where in 1762 graduated from \"Slav-Bulgarian History\".\n%NL% There are about 60 handwritten copies and alteration of Pisiy history, the first was made by Stojko Vladislavov (Sophronius of Vratsa) in 1765 in the town of Kotel.\n%NL% Day the church agreed to be celebrated Reverend Paisij Great June 19.\n%NL%%NL% monastery \"St. George Zograph\" according to legend, was founded at the end of IX or the beginning of the tenth century by three brothers of Bulgarian origin, Moses, Aaron and Ivan Selima from Ohrid.%NL%Now \"Holy Mountain\" - Athos is the largest \"living\" center of Orthodox monasticism.'),(1134,12,'Design - back',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'020512.jpg','Reverse:\n%NL% of Zograph Facsimile copy of \"Slav-Bulgarian History\". This manuscript has been stored in centuries Athonite Monastery \"St. George Zograph.\"\n%NL% Over 80s Zograph draft of \"Slav-Bulgarian History\" disappears and appears in 1996 as an anonymous donation in Bulgaria - the National History Museum.\n%NL% On January 12, 1998, it was formally submitted to the abbot of the monastery, Archimandrite Ambrose Zagrafskiya and return to Athos.\n%NL%%NL% At foreground, the text is placed an image of the signet ring of Tsar Kaloyan (king of Bulgaria in the years 1196-1207), and in the middle of the note, one above the other - three seals with images of the Bulgarian kings - Michael SHishman, Svetoslav Terter and Ivan Asen II.\n%NL% right an upstanding crowned lion of Christopher Zhefarovich from his book \"Stemmatography\".%NL% Zhefarovich a Bulgarian writer, preacher and painter-engraver 17th-18th century, his famous \"Stemmatography\" was published in Vienna in 1741\n%NL% Bottom right depicts the coat of arms of Bulgaria with three lions, published in 1483 in the handwritten Gruenberg heraldic collection.'),(1145,1,'Front',147,100,NULL,NULL,'20051.jpg','The obverse:%NL%%NL% on the obverse are stylized images of architectural fragments from the building of the National Bank.%NL% The right side is seen the statue of St. Nicholas.%NL% In the right light field is a signature of the Governor and the Chief Cashier of the Bank.'),(1145,2,'Back',NULL,NULL,238,95,'20052.jpg','Reverse:\n%NL%\n%NL% in the central area of ??the back is seen the fa?ade of the old building of the Central Bank under it - an image of both sides of the first bill value of 20 lev, published in 1885 in the upper right-hand area is located sculptural image of a seated woman Figure depicting the insertion of 1 and 2 lev, issue 1920, and the right - the coat of arms of the Principality of Bulgaria.\n%NL%'),(1145,3,'Watermark',353,94,59,91,'20053.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%In the bright area of the banknote against the light can be seen three-dimensional halftone image of upright lion, and under him is located contrasting watermark  - the initials “BNB”.\r%NL%\r%NL%\r%NL%'),(1145,4,'Security thread',248,120,157,83,'20054.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% Vertical metallic strip embedded in the paper that comes in part from the reverse side. Visible are cut with special pearlescent coating which changes color between green and purple when changing the angle at which the light falls.\n%NL% against the light, the thread is seen as a continuous dark line printed with her ??negative minitext of repeated \"БНБ 20\".'),(1145,5,'Anti-copier device',52,16,NULL,NULL,'20055.jpg','Prevention stripe:%NL%%NL% vertical, 15 mm wide polymer line on the left side of the face.%NL% Filled with diagonal lines. On it, there are security features: Varifeye ® and holograms.'),(1145,6,'Varifeye ®',52,54,NULL,NULL,'20056.jpg','Varifeye ®:\n%NL%\n%NL% A new