irm of Wagner, produces Bulgarian church in Istanbul \"St. Stephen\", known as \" Iron Church \').'),(1394,3,'Watermark',341,99,61,97,'202k73.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Halftone image of the portrait from the banknote - of Stefan Stambolov.\r%NL%In this emision is included contrasting watermark under the portrait - abbreavition of the central bank - \"BNB\".\r%NL%On penetrating light the two watermark are visible.'),(1394,4,'Security thread, OVI',259,71,149,90,'202k74.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% implanted in the paper strip, which partially comes on the back of the note as a dotted line. Visible rectangles have metallized surface.\n%NL% on the security thread is printed recurring mini-text \"Bank 20\" alternately right and upside down.\n%NL% in the light, is seen as a continuous dark line with a negative mini-text.\n%NL%\n%NL%\n%NL% color shifting ink (OVI):\n%NL%\n%NL% visible sections of the security thread on the back of the note changes color between green and red in case of a tilt towards the light.'),(1394,5,'Anti-copier device',32,95,NULL,NULL,'202k75.jpg','Prevention stripe:%NL%%NL% Vertical holographic stripe on the left side of the obverse. On it in case the inclination to light alternating images of a lion and an eagle;%NL% images of the number \"20\" which pulsates, overflowing in different colors.%NL% On the left side, to the holographic stripe has demetallised strip minitext \"BULGARIAN NATIONAL BANK\" - alternating light areas with dark text and dark areas with light text, and in shallow areas (along the contour of the numbers \"20\") are printed numbers par 20 mini-print.%NL%%NL% on the entire surface of the holographic stripe at the appropriate angle of observation appear parallel to each other sloping lines of text \"BULGARIAN NATIONAL BANK\".%NL%'),(1394,6,'Latent image',58,149,NULL,NULL,'202k76.jpg','Latent image\n%NL%\n%NL% right of prevention stripe observation sharp angle appears the text \"20 ЛЕВА\".\n%NL%'),(1394,7,'See-through regis