. In western Anatolia, there are many places that are associated with the life and death of Yunus Emre. Its researchers believe that 357 of the collected poems poetry archive relative to that era have come under his pen.\n%NL% Yunus Emre is a representative of the so-called. errant Sufis (dervish) - a poet-singers who spread religious folk art, strongly influenced by Islamic mysticism, but based on humanism and the love of neighbor. They often perform their verses in hymns dervish tekkes the accompaniment of music (which is why this branch of Ottoman literature called \"poetry teketata\").\n%NL% Humanistic line in the works of Yunus Emre follow his principles: \"do not raise their hands when they hit, be as dumb as they curse, do not be offended when you hurt your heart ...\"\n%NL%%NL% Fragment of a poem-hymn of Yunus Emre:\n%NL% \"Let\'s all be friends forever\n%NL% let\'s catch and make life wonderful,\n%NL% let us love and beloved -\n%NL%Nobody owns the land. \"'),(1486,2,'Watermark',25,104,406,103,'2h2k92.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Halftone image of the portrait from the banknote and a contrasting image of the number of a nominal 200 aside from the portrait.'),(1486,3,'Security thread',175,151,NULL,NULL,'2h2k93.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% Vertical strip embedded in the paper across the width of the banknote. Is imprinted negative microprinted - repeated \"200TL\" in right and upside down.'),(1486,4,'Holographic strip',410,73,NULL,NULL,'2h2k94.jpg','Holographic stripe\r%NL%\r%NL%A vertical wide band with holographic elements, located on the far right side of the obverse.\r%NL%When changing the viewing angle the colors of the ornaments change, and in the rectangle is alternating image of the letters \"TL\" and the number of par \"200\".'),(1486,5,'Iridescent stripe',NULL,NULL,196,59,'2h2k95.jpg','Iridescent stripe\r%NL%\r%NL%In the middle area of ??the reverse of the banknote is laid an iridescent stripe with sallow pearl luster. For a given viewing angle 