languages. Author of about 20 scientific papers. Most popular in the country book was published in 1824 in Bucharest (with Anton Ivanov) \"Primer of different teachings\" or \"Fish Primer\", so named because the cover depicted dolphin. This is a remarkable book of the Bulgarian Revival, which only in 1862 suffered a further 5 editions. Primer consists of a preamble, section 8, addressing the reader and the application of 12 drawings of animals. This is the first Bulgarian textbook, which proclaim the principles of secular education.\n%NL% Petar Beron ended his life in 1871 is Craiova, Romania.'),(1487,2,'Watermark',350,104,68,89,'102k82.jpg','Watermark (new detail):\r%NL%\r%NL%Three-dimensional halftone image of the portrait of Dr. Peter Beron, under him - contrasting image of the abbreviation of the central bank - \"BNB\" (doesn`t exist in previous emision).\r%NL%The watermark is visible against penetrating light.'),(1487,3,'Security thread',246,117,172,63,'102k83.jpg','Security Thread (change):\n%NL%\n%NL% Vertical metallic thread embedded in the paper, leaving part of the surface, as a dotted line on the reverse side of the banknote. In the light, the thread is dark, continuous, with repeated negative minitext \"Bank 10\". The parts that go on the back of the note changes color from green to reddish-brown when changing the viewing angle. The surface has a pearl sheen.'),(1487,4,'Security thread (new design)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'102k84.jpg','Security thread (new design):\r%NL%\r%NL%a metallized strip woven into the paper with a minitext “БНБ 10” (BNB 10), partially showing through on the reverse side of the banknote, changing colour from green to red at a different viewing angle, when observed through a polarized filter, tilted black and white stripes can be seen on the reverse side of the banknote’s security strip\r%NL%\r%NL%'),(1487,5,'See-through register',298,162,123,161,'102k85.jpg','See through register:\n%NL%\n%NL% A rectangle with staggered squares printe