his death. It is known that his baptismal name was Saul. It is the circle of the disciples of Christ. He was a Pharisee and the spirit of Conservative Judaism participated in the persecution of Christians. Turning him to Christ happened suddenly, resulting in an unusual vision. On the road to Damascus Saul saw an unusual light and heard the voice of God from heaven: \"Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me? ... I am Jesus whom you are persecuting.\" This event was a landmark in his life - he was baptized, took the name Paul and became the most zealous propagator of the Christian faith. Preached in Antioch, Cilicia, Cyprus, Galatea, Ephesus, Athens, Macedonia, Corinth, Spain, and it is called the \"Apostle to the Gentiles.\" Around the 67th year, Paul was chained and sent to Rome for trial. He died a martyr of June 29, 67 along with St. Peter the Apostle. His death was accompanied many miracles. Tradition says that slain by Nero\'s soldiers head of the saint was struck three times on the ground and in these places as soon break out in the spring. Today there is near Rome eponymous monastery \"Three fountain.\"\n%NL%New Testament of the Bible contains fourteen of his messages to the new converts in the faith, which explains Christian values ??and rules of church life.'),(1513,2,'Back',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'052k92.jpg','Reverse: composition from fragments of different pictures of Maestro Ivan Milev - \"Reaper\", \"Dragon\'s wedding\", \"Bulgarian Madonna\", \"bread\".'),(1513,3,'Watermark',360,100,71,95,'052k93.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Halftone image of the portrait from the banknote - of Ivan Milev.\r%NL%In this emision is included a watermark under the portrait - abbreviation of the central bank - \"BNB\".\r%NL%Equilly clearly visible from the both sides of the banknote, against penetrating light.'),(1513,4,'Security thread',250,48,167,35,'052k94.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% implantation in metallized paper strip, which partially comes on the back of the note