nze vessel (something like a bucket) with engraved vurhu it Greek motifs. Was found in the excavation of a small hill in the northeast of the island Myung at the beginning of the 19th Century (October 1827). The Court has a sleek design, surely Greek and probably was made in Macedonia or anywhere near the Black Sea in the fourth or early third century BC Probably come across these lands during the military campaigns in Europe.\n%NL%Now artifact is stored in the National Museum in Copenhagen.'),(1577,3,'Watermark',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5h113.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Represents stylish halftone image of a viking ship Skuldelev and contrasting number of nominal 500. \r%NL%\r%NL%'),(1577,4,'3D Security thread',195,84,265,101,'5h114.jpg','3D Secure Threat:\r%NL%\r%NL%Ribbon implanted in the paper leaving a partial on the reverse side of the banknote in the form of dashed lines. On the visible areas are \"moving\" left-right and up-down pattern. Illusion of motion (3D) was created by a special process of printing and would be difficult to replicate by counterfeiters.%NL%%NL% against visible light continuous band of light and dark areas.'),(1577,5,'Security thread',374,25,68,18,'5h115.jpg','security Thread\n%NL%\n%NL% fully inserted within the paper vertical filament which is visible against the light penetrating equally clear from both sides of the banknote.'),(1577,6,'Hologram',42,160,NULL,NULL,'5h116.jpg','Hologram\r%NL%\r%NL%Has the form and elements of ancient Greek bronze vessel shown on the reverse side of the banknote. When changing the viewing angle on it appears an image of the number of nominal 500 and ornaments in and around the circle change their color.\r%NL%In considering under a magnifying glass can be seen that contours surrounding the container are composed of repeating microtext \"KR500\".'),(1577,7,'Intaglio printing',57,27,NULL,NULL,'5h117.jpg','embossing\n%NL%\n%NL% of the bridge image and the text \"500 FEM HUNDREDE KRONER\" are printed using the \