d build between 1988 and 1996, consists of two separate tunnels with one line each. The length is 8024 m.%NL% western (lower) bridge was built in the period 1989-1994 and combines two parallel lanes - for road and rail traffic. Length: 6611 m.%NL%%NL% total length of the Great Belt (excluding the intermediate island) is 13.5 km.'),(1588,2,'Back',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1t112.jpg','Reverse:%NL%%NL% \"sun chariot\" - this is the artifact, which is dedicated to the design of the reverse side. Found by chance in 1902 when plowing Trundholm swamp on the island Sheland.%NL% A bronze statue of a horse pulling a disc, which is believed to be a model of the sun. The artefact is of high quality and is dated to the Early Bronze Age, c. 1400 BC%NL% statuette is 23 inches long, the disc diameter is 25 cm, gold is on one side and the elegant spiral and circular decorations. Sun chariot illustrates the ancient belief that in its infinite movement sun is drawn by the heavenly horses.%NL%%NL% solar chariot is one of the most valuable exhibits of the National Museum of Denmark in Copenhagen.%NL% the place where in 1902 it was discovered artifact is now a memorial.%NL%'),(1588,3,'Watermark',105,80,NULL,NULL,'1t113.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Represents stylish halftone image of a viking ship Skuldelev and contrasting number of a nominal 1000 in bottom. \r%NL%\r%NL%\r%NL%\r%NL%'),(1588,4,'3D Security thread',188,85,269,105,'1t114.jpg','3D Secure Threat\r%NL%\r%NL%Ribbon implanted in the paper leaving a partial on the reverse side of the banknote in the form of dashed lines. On the visible areas are \"moving\" left-right and up-down pattern. Illusion of motion (3D) was created by a special process of printing and would be difficult to replicate by counterfeiters.%NL%%NL% against visible light continuous band of light and dark areas.'),(1588,5,'Security thread',365,91,92,104,'1t115.jpg','security Thread\n%NL%\n%NL% fully inserted within the paper vertical filament which is visible against t