ent window 1 and hidden symbols:%NL%%NL%An element of the security of polymer banknotes - maple leaf.%NL%%NL% %NL%%NL%!!!Look at the frosted maple leaf window to see that it has a transparent outline.'),(1592,3,'Transparent window 2',319,40,105,60,'50113.jpg','A transparent window 2:\r%NL%\r%NL%A wide strip with uneven contours in the right area (at observation to the front). It combines and other security features - holographic images, transparent text.'),(1592,4,'Transparent text',330,100,110,92,'50114.jpg','A transparent text:\r%NL%\r%NL%In the vertical translucent band is located text \"CANADA 50\" - also transparent and readable from both sides.'),(1592,5,'Hologram',328,150,100,150,'50115.jpg','Hologram\r%NL%\r%NL%On the transparent strip are printed metalized high resolution images possessing optical properties - the portrait from the banknote (William Lyon Mackenzie King) and a tower - can be seen on both sides of the banknote.'),(1592,6,'See-through register',375,158,52,165,'50116.jpg','See through register:\n%NL%\n%NL% The given fragment of the ornaments on the front and back completely overlap when the banknote against the penetrating light.'),(1592,7,'Microprint',84,177,425,90,'50117.jpg','Microtexts\r%NL%\r%NL%Text \"BANK OF CANADA 50 BANQUE DU CANADA 50\"is integrated in the background on the front side.\r%NL%\r%NL%Теxts \"BANK OF CANADA\" (Engl.) и \"BANQUE DU CANADA\" (Fr.) at the left and right side of the back are legible under a magnifying glass.'),(1592,8,'Intaglio printing',42,130,NULL,NULL,'50118.jpg','embossing\n%NL%\n%NL% is enclosed on the obverse.'),(1605,1,'Watermark',43,112,365,113,'50113.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Hold the 50 GBP note up to the light and you will see an image of the Queen\'s portrait together with a bright L50.'),(1605,2,'Motion thread',125,112,292,32,'50114.jpg','Motion Thread:\r%NL%\r%NL%The motion thread on the 50 GBP note is woven into the paper. It has five windows along its length which contain images of the  L symbol and the number 50. When the note is tilted from side to side, the images move up and down. When the note is tilted up and down, the images move from side to side and the number 50 and Ј symbol switch.'),(1605,3,'Security thread',247,46,NULL,NULL,'50115.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% Metallic thread embedded in the paper. If you hold the note up to the light the thread will appear as a continuous dark line.'),(1605,4,'See-through register',90,110,319,104,'50116.jpg','See-through register - hold the 50 GBP note up to the light and you will see coloured irregular shapes printed on the front and back that combine to form the L symbol.'),(1605,5,'Raised print',145,31,NULL,NULL,'50117.jpg','Raised print - by running your finger across the front of the Ј50 note you can feel raised print in areas such as the words \'Bank of England\' and in the bottom right corner, around the number 50.'),(1605,6,'Raised print',375,160,NULL,NULL,'50118.jpg','Raised print - by running your finger across the front of the Ј50 note you can feel raised print in areas such as the words \'Bank of England\' and in the bottom right corner, around the number 50.'),(1605,7,'Raised print',370,29,NULL,NULL,'501101.jpg','Raised print - by running your finger across the front of the Ј50 note you can feel raised print in areas such as the words \'Bank of England\' and in the bottom right corner, around the number 50.'),(1605,8,'UV detail',196,24,NULL,NULL,'50119.jpg','Ultra-violet feature - if you look at the front of the 50 GBP note under a good quality ultra-violet light the number 50 appears in bright red and green. The five windows of the motion thread also appear in bright green. Randomly spread bright red and green flecks are also visible on both the front and back of the note. The remainder of the note appears dull in contrast.'),(1605,9,'Microprint',211,80,NULL,NULL,'501111.jpg','Microlettering - using a magnifying glass, look closely at the lettering beneath the Queen\'s portrait on the Ј5