\n%NL%%NL%%NL%Neuschwanstein (translated as \"New swan Rock\") is the most fabulous of all the castles on the ground. Located near F?ssen - the border between Germany and Austria at the foot of the highest peak Zugspitz German. The town is the end of the famous Romantic road built by the Romans and connected the most beautiful places of the province.\n%NL%Neuschwanstein was built on the idea of ??Ludwig II of Bavaria (1845-1886), King of Bavaria from 1864 to 1886, also called the Swan Knight (and Ludwig \"foolish\"). Architects and Georg Riedel Edward Dolman. In 1869, laid the first stone of Neuschwanstein. The construction takes him in \'17 in a letter to Ludwig II to Richard Wagner, he reveals his desire to build a castle that will remind you of \"Lohengrin\" and \"Tannh?user.\" And succeeds (is finalized after the death of Ludwig II). The castle is magnificent. It is decorated with scenes from medieval legends, including the King\'s favorite legend swan knight (Lohengrin, with whom he identifies). The walls of the hall depicts the saga of Siegfried. Throne Hall is modeled on the hall where Percival kept a Holy Grail. Royal bedroom is decorated with scenes from the myth of Tristan and Isolde. Cabinets of Ludwig II in the Romanesque style, with finely carved oak walls. Exquisite tapestries were created by the famous Joseph Aigner and illustrate the legend of Tannh?user. Hall singers occupies the entire fourth floor of the castle. Besides the paintings on the walls in her huge gilded candlesticks and chandeliers hanging ... Neuschwanstein has more than 360 rooms.\n%NL% present castle is a museum and is one of the most popular in Europe - visit it each year more than 1.3 million people.'),(1616,1,'Watermark',390,94,42,101,'5t101.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Halftone image of portraif of Earl N. Muravyov and vertically located contrasting number of nominal 5000.'),(1616,2,'Security thread',67,40,355,89,'5t102.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% implanted in the paper strip with a width of 5 mm. On the face it comes to the surface in a window with ornamental form (stained window). On it there is a mini-text \"5000\" printed with special metallic ink with an optical effect. From the other side looks like a matte gray tape. In the light, visible as a dark line.\n%NL%\n%NL%'),(1616,3,'Holographic images',67,85,NULL,NULL,'5t103.jpg','Holographic images\r%NL%\r%NL%The images on the security thread on the front side (\"5000\") have a holographic effect. \r%NL%When changing the slope towards the light individual digits of the numbers \"5000\" change brightness and  color and seemed to be moving.'),(1616,4,'SPARK security feature',310,52,NULL,NULL,'5t104.jpg','Security Feature Spark:\n%NL%%NL% Shiny foil shape and image of the coat of arms of the city of Khabarovsk. When you change the angle of view changes the brightness and luster, creating the illusion of movement.\n%NL%%NL% SPARK ® technology was developed by Swiss company SICPA, specialized in the field of special inks and technologies applicable to identification documents, notes, etc.\n%NL%%NL% SPARK ® can create several unique dynamic visual effects:\n%NL% - \"moving\" color: when changing the viewing angle dark and light areas change places;\n%NL% - \"overflow\" of light outside shape of the design;\n%NL% - 3D effect.\n%NL% SPARK ® is an optical instrument for the protection based on specific OVMI ® - ink. It contains visual pigment change is created by vacuum technology. The pigment is composed of thin layers and the middle layer is magnetic.\n%NL%%NL% SPARK ® does not \"stick\" to the paper and is created during printing, making it difficult to reproduce and therefore very safe security element.'),(1616,5,'Anti-copier device',130,95,NULL,NULL,'5t105.jpg','Anti-copy security element (moire):%NL%%NL% by tilting the banknote against the light \"window\" appear stripes with the colors of the rainbow.\n%NL% at the bottom of the ornament has a field with constantly visible part of the color banding (MVC + effect).'),(1616,6,'Microperforation',320,95,NULL,NULL,'5t106.jpg','Microperforation:\r%NL%\r%NL%When the banknote is held up to the source of light, one can view the note denomination \"5000\" formed by absolutely straight parallel rows of holes perforated in the paper. The area of a banknote with the holes does not feel rough to the touch.'),(1616,7,'Hidden image',290,130,NULL,NULL,'5t107.jpg','Hidden image:\r%NL%\r%NL%The letters \"PP\" (Russian Ruble) - ie. \"KIPP-effect\" On the bar at the bottom right area of ??the face at a specific viewing angle.'),(1616,8,'Intaglio printing',345,10,NULL,NULL,'5t108.jpg','Embossing:\n%NL%\n%NL% on the obverse.'),(1616,9,'Microprint',270,29,190,138,'5t109.jpg','Microtexts:\r%NL%\r%NL%Integrated into the design on the front and reverse side - easily legible under a magnifying glass.'),(1616,10,'IR image',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5t1010.jpg','IR image\n%NL%\n%NL% image on the front and back of the banknote under infrared light.'),(1616,11,'Magnetic areas',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5t1011.jpg','Magnetic areas:\r%NL%\r%NL%some elements of the image have magnetic properties.'),(1619,1,'Watermark',385,79,43,101,'5h101.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%\r%NL%Multitone image of portrait of Peter the Great and contrasting image of the number of a nominal - 500.'),(1619,2,'Security thread',83,33,350,105,'5h102.jpg','Security thread:\n%NL%\n%NL% implantation in metallized paper strip, 5 mm wide with micro text printed on it - straight and reversed numbers separated by 500 diamonds.\n%NL% From the reverse side (resting on a solid surface) thread is visible as a dark gray bar microprinted and observation for penetrating light numbers and lozenges are bright on a dark background (negative).'),(1619,3,'Hologram',72,80,NULL,NULL,'5h103.jpg','Hologram:\r%NL%\r%NL%The visible part of the security thread that comes in stained glass window on the front side has a coating that has holographic properties. When the banknote is tilted, you can see 