te.','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%The imitated watermark is different, seems flat and is formed with light and dark fields which are visible after\r%NL%illuminated by ultraviolet light. Stained brownish and it lacks an image of the the number \"50\", which is an integral part of the original watermark. In some counterfeits the watermark\r is displaced in comparison to the position in the original notes.\r%NL%'),(40,2,'Raised print',87,169,116,204,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%With fingertips is felt an embossment in the texts in the portrait and the sign for blind people.','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%It does not feel an embossment in the texts, in the portrait and visually impaired sign.'),(40,3,'Security thread',162,0,199,220,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%When observing against the light, the thread is visible as a continuous line with \r predetermined width and thickness. It can be seen the light microtext \"50 DM\". The thread is embedded in the paper and appear on the front side at intervals 5 mm.','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%Partially extending security thread is imitated by short dashes, that is clearly visible when observing against the light. There is no the light micro-text \"50 DM\" too.\r%NL%'),(40,4,'See-through register',200,21,228,51,232,20,262,47,'','','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%When observing against the light, in the hexagonsee-through register is well  formed the letter \"D\" .The text in the zone \"50 DM\" is readable.','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%In the hexagon -see-through register, printed in the upper central part of the front of the banknote, when observing against the light, it does not form the letter \"D\" well . The microtext in the zone \"50 DM\", the walls of the hexagonsee-through register.'),(40,5,'Microtext',368,13,412,134,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%===========================\r%NL%The text \"FUNFZIG\" is readable.','\r%NL%==========================\r%NL%The text \"FUNFZIG\" in the zone with oblique stripes behind the portrait on the front side of the note is illegible.'),(40,6,'Hidden image',413,55,435,132,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%===========================\r%NL%It can be seen the hidden image - the initials \"DM\".','\r%NL%===========================\r%NL%It is not visible the latent image - the initials \"DM\".\r%NL%'),(40,7,'Microtext',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,241,131,345,195,'','','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%The text is readable at hatches of the numbers of the nominal.','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%The microtext \"50 DM\" is illegible at the hatch in the figures of the nominal.\r%NL%\r%NL%'),(41,1,'Watermark',11,40,100,147,348,48,435,176,'','','\r%NL%==========================\r%NL%I.In the original banknotes the portrait - watermark seems three-dimensional, and on irradiation under ultraviolet light is invisible. Below it is shown the nominal value of the banknote also.','\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%I.The imitated watermark is different from the original, it seems flat and shaped with contour dark or pale brown or beige lines, or dark and light fields that are visible when illuminating with UV-light. In some counterfeits is missing an image with the number \"100\", which is an integral part of the original watermark. The portrait - watermark can be different in size or displaced by the one in the original notes.\r%NL%-----------------------------\r%NL%II.The imitated watermark looks flat and shaped with contour lines that in monitoring with ultraviolet light is invisible or less visible. The mimicked watermark differs in configuration and size from the original image\r воден знак.\r%NL%-----------------------------\r%NL%The watermark is printed in white and is not transparent through the paper.\r%NL%'),(41,2,'Raised print',110,15,158,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%==========================\r%N