ickness. The integrated security thread is displayed on the front side at an interval of 5 mm.','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%I.Partially coming out security thread is imitated by short dashes, which is clearly visible in monitoring against the light. On the simulated thread is missing the bright microtext \"100 DM\", which appears in the original thread.\r%NL%-----------------------------\r%NL%II.The partially coming out security thread is imitated by a whole strip of wider and thicker foil in which is missing the bright microtext.\r%NL%-----------------------------\r%NL%In some counterfeits on the thread is noticeable the unsuccessful attempt to\r%NL%imitate the inscription\"100DM\".\r%NL%-----------------------------\r%NL%There are also counterfaits with built WHOLE security thread, BUT OTHER ELEMENTS OF PROTECTION ARE NOT QUALITATIVE.\r%NL%'),(41,6,'Microtext',375,10,408,125,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%The microtext in this area is well legible.','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%The microtext \"HUNDERT\" is illegible.\r%NL%'),(41,7,'Hidden image',413,62,436,126,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%The latent image - the initials \"DM\" is clearly visible.','\r%NL%=============================\r%NL%It is not visible the latent image - the initials \"DM\".\r%NL%'),(41,8,'Microtext',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,228,134,333,191,'','','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%In the hatch at the figures of the nominal value on the reverse side is legible  the microtext, respectively \"100 DM\".','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%In the hatch at the figures of the nominal value on the reverse side the microtext, respectively \"100 DM\", is illegible.\r%NL%'),(42,1,'Watermark',12,36,99,150,359,56,446,188,'','','\r%NL%==========================\r%NL%In the original notes-the portrait watermark seems three-dimensional and when illuminating with ultraviolet light\r%NL%remains invisible. Below it is displayed also the number of nominal.','\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%The imitated watermark is different from the original. It looks flat and is formed with light and dark fields which are visible after illumination with ultraviolet light. In some counterfeits is missing the image of the number \"200\", which is an integral part of the original watermark and the portrait-watermark can be shifted in comparison to the position in the original notes.\r%NL%\r%NL%'),(42,2,'Raised print',71,163,108,196,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%It is felt an embossment in the texts in the portrait and in the sign for blind people.','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%With fingertips does not feel the embossment which the original notes is found in the the texts, in the sign for blind citizens in the portrait and other.'),(42,3,'Raised print',108,17,135,138,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%==========================\r%NL%There is felt an embossment in the texts in the portrait and the sign for blind people.','\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%With fingertips does not feel the embossment which the original notes is found in the the texts, in the sign for blind citizens in the portrait and other.'),(42,4,'See-through register',147,22,178,51,283,24,309,47,'','','\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%In the hexagon-see-through register, when observing against the light, is formed the letter \"D\".','\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%In the hexagon-see-through register, when observing against the light, is not formed letter \"D\". The microtext \"200 DM\" is not readable on the sides of the hexagon, on thesee-through register on the obverse and the reverse side.'),(42,5,'See-through register',183,0,222,206,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','\r%NL%============================\r%NL%The partially protruding thread appears as a continuous line with a specified width and thickness when illuminating with light. Onto the fibers is visible