o1p2.jpg','1h96f1p2.jpg','Watermark:\r%NL%If the banknote is held against the light, the portrait and the value of the note below it are visible as an watermark.','Watermark:\r%NL%The photocopies fail to reproduce the watermark, although it can be simulated by printing after copying (left half).'),(48,3,'Security thread',186,2,223,212,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h96o1p3.jpg','1h96f1p3.jpg','Security thread:\r%NL%The banknotes have a security thread showing the value of the note. The thread is visible in several \"windows\" and has a silver gleam when the banknote is viewed from above. When the banknote is placed against the light (in the illustration), the thread appears as a continuous dark line. Continuously repeated value numeral on the thread alternate in a right and a mirror image. ','Security thread:\r%NL%Top view: \"the windows\" are predominantly dark. In case of a glossy imitation, the value of the banknote, in most cases is not visible. \r%NL%View against the light (in the illustration): The thread in most cases is not fully reproduced. Missing continuously recurring image of the value of the banknote.'),(48,4,'See-through register',147,24,177,52,284,24,316,49,'1h96o1p4.jpg','1h96f1p4.jpg','See-through register:\r%NL%Irregular shapes are scattered within a hexagon on the front and back side of the note. When the banknote is placed against the light, they combine to form a letter \"D\".\r%NL%','See-through register:\r%NL%Insufficiently accurate correspondence between the figures gives a blurred image.'),(48,5,'Hidden image',409,61,433,155,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h96o1p5.jpg','1h96f1p5.jpg','Hidden image:\r%NL%In the color band at bottom part of the banknote are written the letters \"DM\". They can not be seen except when the banknote is held horizontally at eye level to light and slowly rotated at this position. \r%NL%','Hidden image:\r%NL%Irrelevant in how many directions is rotated the counterfeit, the letters \"DM\" do not appear. '),(48,6,'Microtext',373,13,402,103,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h96o1p6.jpg','1h96f1p6.jpg','\r%NL%========================\r%NL%The separate letters and numbers are indistinguishable, they just merge into one another.','\r%NL%========================\r%NL%The banknote contains the following text, which can be seen with a magnifying glass: value numeral \"HUNDERT\" between the portrait and the color ribbon and \"100 DM\" as well as a framework of the see-through register and in great quantity of the rear part of the banknote. '),(48,7,'Fluorescence',253,2,356,211,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1h96o1p7.jpg','1h96f1p7.jpg','\r%NL%=========================At ultraviolet light the following elements emit light: \r%NL%\r%NL%I.Part of the view from the town \r%NL%\r%NL%-----------------------------\r%NL%II.Numbers of the banknote \r%NL%\r%NL%----------------------------\r%NL%III.The colored fibers embedded in the paper (red, blue and yellow). The paper itself is not fluorescent (not emit light).\r%NL%','\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%In case of a forgerypractically the entire surface of the paper illuminates, separate parts of the banknote do not usually fluoresce (do not emit light).'),(69,1,'Defect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,21,41,48,'','1093f1p1.jpg','\r%NL%========================\r%NL%The fine line shading has thin, distinct lines without merging and spotting.','Printing defects\r%NL%========================\r%NL%There are two purple points in the frame on the left side.'),(69,2,'Defect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,76,43,117,71,'','1093f1p2.jpg','\r%NL%========================\r%NL%The fine line shading has thin, distinct lines without merging and spotting.','Printing defects\r%NL%=========================\r%NL%There is a red dot in the background at right of the flag, under the tree leaves.'),(69,3,'Defect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,257,189,293,216,'','1093f1p3.jpg','\r%NL%========================\r%NL%There are no spots and dots.','Printing defects\r%NL%========================\r%NL%There are small dots to the right of th